The ab benchmark program that ships with httpd can benchmark SSL sites, if you build with CFLAGS="-
DUSE_SSL" LDFLAGS="-lssl -lcrypto". However, the SSL code in ab.c (below) restricts the connections to 
the obsolete SSL protocol version 2. When the constructor function is replaced by 
SSLv23_client_method(), ab will automatically choose the highest SSL/TLS version the underlying 
OpenSSL library has to offer. 

Index: src/support/ab.c
===============================================================
====
--- src/support/ab.c    (revision 125243)
+++ src/support/ab.c    (working copy)
@@ -1655,7 +1655,7 @@

 #ifdef USE_SSL
     SSL_library_init();
-    if (!(ctx = SSL_CTX_new(SSLv2_client_method()))) {
+    if (!(ctx = SSL_CTX_new(SSLv23_client_method()))) {
        fprintf(stderr, "Could not init SSL CTX: ");
        ERR_print_errors_fp(stderr);
        exit(1);
